    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix timespec normalization bug causing invalid time comparisons\n\n### Summary\nThe `time_add` functions in the tracer module were using `>` instead of `>=` when checking if nanosecond values needed normalization. This caused timespec structures with exactly 1000000000 nanoseconds to remain unnormalized, creating invalid timespec values that led to unexpected behavior in `time_cmp`.\n\nThis fix changes the comparison operator from `>` to `>=` in both `time.c` and `ticktime.c` files, ensuring proper normalization of timespec values.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/view/time.c`: Fixed timespec normalization in `time_add` function (line 41)\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/view/ticktime.c`: Fixed timespec normalization in `time_add` function (line 48)\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Create two timespec values that when added together result in exactly 1000000000 nanoseconds\n2. Call the `time_add` function with these values\n3. Pass the result to `time_cmp` for comparison with another timespec\n4. Observe unexpected comparison results due to the invalid timespec structure\n\nThe invalid timespec would have tv_nsec = 1000000000 instead of being normalized to tv_sec += 1 and tv_nsec = 0, causing `time_cmp` to produce incorrect results when comparing such values.\n"
}